{"type":"message","id":"7060e020","parentId":"e6de9b30","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:18:52.064Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The global file shows `strategy_max_dd_pct = 24.51` and `halt_new_buy = true`. This is the shared global halt that's causing all three panels to be stopped.\n\nNow I need to generate per-panel runtime risk state files with different halt thresholds:\n- aggressive: halt at 35% drawdown (so with 24.51% drawdown, it would NOT be halted)\n- balanced: halt at 28% drawdown (so with 24.51% drawdown, it would NOT be halted)\n- defensive: halt at 15% drawdown (so with 24.51% drawdown, it WOULD be halted - same as current)\n\n\nThe key is calculating each panel's individual drawdown using its specific max drawdown and halt thresholds, since they all share the same underlying metrics like breadth and index return but differ only in their tolerance levels.\n\nNow I'm realizing the per-panel halt files are empty `{}`, which means the pipeline never actually populated them—I need to check how `apply_risk_to_signals.py` and `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py` are supposed to generate these files and why the population step is missing.","thinkingSignature":"2f8be5cce8af064489070cd7ee928ef52919d1eb21194e55c5beefcd6208f7aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ouerdspg3d9t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -l \"runtime_risk_state_latest_aggressive\\|runtime_risk_state_latest_balanced\\|runtime_risk_state_latest_defensive\" scripts/*.py research/reports/*.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7348,"output":335,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32915,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774991924680,"responseId":"061b6d34d1aec6364ea0d451decc6326"}}
