{"type":"message","id":"2715b1ac","parentId":"6eeadb82","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:09.871Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8a38gubmflqw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    live_config = load_json(live_config_path)\n    risk_payload = load_json(Path(args.risk_config).expanduser().resolve()) if args.risk_config else {}\n    runtime_inputs = enrich_runtime_inputs(\n        trade_date=args.trade_date,\n        live_config=live_config,\n        market_breadth=args.market_breadth,\n        index_ret_pct=args.index_ret_pct,\n        strategy_max_dd_pct=args.strategy_max_dd_pct,\n        strategy_sharpe=args.strategy_sharpe,\n    )\n\n    engine = RiskEngine(build_risk_config(risk_payload, live_config=live_config))\n    context = RiskContext(\n        trade_date=args.trade_date,\n        market_breadth=runtime_inputs[\"market_breadth\"],\n        risk_off=args.risk_off,\n        hard_stop=args.hard_stop,\n        available_cash=args.available_cash,\n        account_nav=args.account_nav,\n        index_ret_pct=runtime_inputs[\"index_ret_pct\"],\n        strategy_max_drawdown_pct=runtime_inputs[\"strategy_max_dd_pct\"],\n        strategy_sharpe=runtime_inputs[\"strategy_sharpe\"],\n        style_smallcap_short_return_pct=parse_float(\n            (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"smallcap_short_return_pct\"),\n            0.0,\n        ) if (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"smallcap_short_return_pct\") is not None else None,\n        style_smallcap_medium_return_pct=parse_float(\n            (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"smallcap_medium_return_pct\"),\n            0.0,\n        ) if (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"smallcap_medium_return_pct\") is not None else None,\n        style_short_excess_pct=parse_float(\n            (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"short_excess_pct\"),\n            0.0,\n        ) if (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"short_excess_pct\") is not None else None,\n        style_medium_excess_pct=parse_float(\n            (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"medium_excess_pct\"),\n            0.0,\n        ) if (runtime_inputs.get(\"style_snapshot\") or {}).get(\"medium_excess_pct\") is not None else None,\n    )\n\n    approved = engine.apply(merged, context)\n    runtime_decision = engine.evaluate_runtime_state(context)\n\n    merged_signal_type = merged.get(\"signal_type\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).fillna(\"\").astype(str).str.upper().str.strip()\n    buy_frame = merged.loc[merged_signal_type.isin(BUY_SIGNAL_TYPES)].copy() if not merged.empty else pd.DataFrame()\n    candidate_codes = {\n        normalize_ts_code(code)\n        for code in buy_frame.get(\"ts_code\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).tolist()\n        if normalize_ts_code(code)\n    }\n    buy_score_map = {}\n    if not buy_frame.empty and \"score\" in buy_frame.columns:\n        buy_score_map = {\n            normalize_ts_code(row.ts_code): parse_float(row.score, 0.0)\n            for row in buy_frame[[\"ts_code\", \"score\"]].itertuples(index=False)\n            if normalize_ts_code(row.ts_code)\n        }\n\n    execution_cfg = (live_config.get(\"execution\", {}) or {}) if isinstance(live_config, dict) else {}\n    lot_size = max(1, int(parse_float(execution_cfg.get(\"lot_size\"), 100)))\n    holdings_path = Path(args.holdings).expanduser().resolve() if args.holdings else None\n    trade_history_path = Path(args.trade_history).expanduser().resolve() if args.trade_history else None\n    exit_signals, exit_summary = generate_exit_signals(\n        trade_date=args.trade_date,\n        account_nav=args.account_nav,\n        mode=runtime_decision.mode,\n        live_config=live_config,\n        project_root=PROJECT_ROOT,\n        report_dir=PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\",\n        holdings_path=holdings_path,\n        trade_history_path=trade_history_path,\n        lot_size=lot_size,\n        candidate_codes=candidate_codes,\n        buy_score_map=buy_score_map,\n    )\n\n    combined_approved = validate_signal_frame(\n        merge_exit_signals(approved, exit_signals),\n        context=\"apply_risk_to_merged_signals:combined_approved\",\n    )\n\n[44 more lines in file. Use offset=400 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774991949862}}
{"type":"message","id":"9afcb8bc","parentId":"2715b1ac","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:16.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand how the runtime halt decision is made. The key is in `engine.evaluate_runtime_state(context)` and `engine.apply(merged, context)`. Let me check the `RiskEngine` class to understand how it evaluates the halt condition.\n\nBut more importantly, I need to understand the overall flow for T05. The blueprint says:\n1. Generate per-panel runtime risk truth files (populate the empty aggressive/balanced/defensive json files)\n2. Scripts that use runtime risk state should use per-panel versions\n\nLet me first write a script to generate the per-panel runtime risk state files, using the global file as base but applying per-panel thresholds. Then I need to update the scripts that consume these files.\n\n\nI'll create a population script that reads the global runtime state, applies each panel's specific thresholds to determine their halt conditions, and writes out the per-panel files. The `runtime_decision` object from `RiskEngine.evaluate_runtime_state()` will be my reference for what needs to go into each file.","thinkingSignature":"cdc066f8ab7a4ddba63c20826671d2367d7b0f3ebe03a9e8188e4bfc40c83578"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wodvkrtdaqqt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -n \"def evaluate_runtime_state\\|def apply\\|strategy_max_drawdown_halt\\|halt_new_buy\" scripts/apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10965,"output":296,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774991949871,"responseId":"061b6d4e6dd7a555eeea699989dc7ec8"}}
