{"type":"message","id":"cf1d7879","parentId":"9a712b45","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:23.276Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iaa07zqv1m96_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"37:    strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct: Optional[float] = None\n69:    halt_new_buy: bool\n107:    def evaluate_runtime_state(self, context: RiskContext) -> RiskDecision:\n167:        max_dd_th = self.config.strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\n181:            halt_new_buy = True\n184:            halt_new_buy = not self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\n187:            halt_new_buy = False\n190:            halt_new_buy = False\n196:            halt_new_buy=halt_new_buy,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"37:    strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct: Optional[float] = None\n69:    halt_new_buy: bool\n107:    def evaluate_runtime_state(self, context: RiskContext) -> RiskDecision:\n167:        max_dd_th = self.config.strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\n181:            halt_new_buy = True\n184:            halt_new_buy = not self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\n187:            halt_new_buy = False\n190:            halt_new_buy = False\n196:            halt_new_buy=halt_new_buy,","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774991963269}}
{"type":"message","id":"208a7fc7","parentId":"cf1d7879","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:44.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the logic. The `RiskEngine.evaluate_runtime_state()` uses `self.config.strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` as a threshold. If the current drawdown >= this threshold, it triggers `halt_new_buy`.\n\nSo for the per-panel files:\n- aggressive: halt threshold = 35%, current drawdown = 24.51% → halt = False (no halt!)\n- balanced: halt threshold = 28%, current drawdown = 24.51% → halt = False\n- defensive: halt threshold = 15%, current drawdown = 24.51% → halt = True (halted, same as current)\n\n\nThe per-panel files should override the halt conditions with these panel-specific thresholds, while keeping other metrics like market breadth and volatility unchanged. The cleanest approach is to generate the three per-panel runtime risk state files with their respective halt logic, then update the scripts to read from these panel-specific files when available instead of the global one.\n\nNow I need to write the script that populates these per-panel files and modifies the script paths accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"2f561d854f4f23fb4624ef4086d96ff2773ccd28b88a57dfc9d131c9fc613db8"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. The per-panel runtime risk files are empty `{}` — the core blocker. I need to populate them with per-panel halt thresholds, then update the consuming scripts. Let me execute T05.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ngg9al0obe6s_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nT05 Step 1: Generate per-panel runtime risk state files.\nReads the global runtime_risk_state_latest.json as base,\nthen applies per-panel thresholds from panel_profile_registry,\nwriting aggressive/balanced/defensive variants.\n\"\"\"\nimport json, sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).parent.parent\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nsys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n\nfrom scripts.panel_profile_registry import PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG\n\ndef load_global_risk():\n    path = REPORT_DIR / \"runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n    if not path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Global runtime risk state not found: {path}\")\n    with open(path) as f:\n        return json.load(f)\n\ndef compute_panel_risk(global_risk: dict, profile_slug: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build a per-panel runtime risk state with panel-level halt logic.\"\"\"\n    cfg = PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG.get(profile_slug, {})\n    halt_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\", 15.0)\n    riskoff_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\", 10.0)\n    \n    global_metrics = global_risk.get(\"runtime_metrics\", {})\n    current_dd = global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)\n    \n    # Panel-level halt decision\n    halt_new_buy = current_dd >= halt_pct\n    risk_off = current_dd >= riskoff_pct\n    \n    # Gate reasons\n    gate_reasons = []\n    if risk_off:\n        gate_reasons.append(f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {riskoff_pct:.4f}\")\n    if halt_new_buy:\n        gate_reasons.append(f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= HALT_THRESHOLD({halt_pct:.4f})\")\n    \n    # Build the panel runtime risk state\n    panel_risk = {\n        **global_risk,\n        \"generated_at\": global_risk.get(\"generated_at\", \"\"),\n        \"panel\": profile_slug,\n        \"panel_halt_threshold_pct\": halt_pct,\n        \"panel_riskoff_threshold_pct\": riskoff_pct,\n        \"runtime_metrics\": {\n            **global_metrics,\n            \"panel_strategy_max_dd_pct\": current_dd,\n        },\n        \"base_runtime\": {\n            **(global_risk.get(\"base_runtime\") or {}),\n            \"mode\": \"cautious\" if risk_off else (\"normal\" if not halt_new_buy else \"halted\"),\n            \"halt_new_buy\": halt_new_buy,\n            \"risk_off\": risk_off,\n            \"halt_reason\": f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {halt_pct:.4f}\" if halt_new_buy else \"\",\n            \"gate_reasons\": gate_reasons,\n        },\n        \"note\": f\"Per-panel runtime risk truth for {profile_slug}: halt>@{halt_pct}%(dd={current_dd}%), riskoff>@{riskoff_pct}%\",\n    }\n    return panel_risk\n\ndef main():\n    global_risk = load_global_risk()\n    \n    for profile_slug in [\"aggressive\", \"balanced\", \"defensive\"]:\n        panel_risk = compute_panel_risk(global_risk, profile_slug)\n        out_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"runtime_risk_state_latest_{profile_slug}.json\"\n        with open(out_path, \"w\") as f:\n            json.dump(panel_risk, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n        \n        br = panel_risk[\"base_runtime\"]\n        print(f\"  {profile_slug}: halt={br['halt_new_buy']}, risk_off={br['risk_off']}, \"\n              f\"halt_pct={panel_risk['panel_halt_threshold_pct']}%, dd={global_risk['runtime_metrics']['strategy_max_dd_pct']}%\")\n    \n    print(f\"\\nGenerated 3 per-panel runtime risk files in {REPORT_DIR}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_per_panel_runtime_risk_t05.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11670,"output":1233,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38135,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774991963276,"responseId":"061b6d5b15e6d5df4ebc5fc5ed089891"}}
