{"type":"message","id":"dc518da8","parentId":"faeca22a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:53.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The per-panel runtime risk files are now populated:\n- aggressive: halt=False, risk_off=False → can buy!\n- balanced: halt=False, risk_off=True → can buy (but risk_off mode)\n- defensive: halt=True, risk_off=True → same as current, halted\n\nThis is exactly what we want. Now I need to update the scripts that use `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` to use per-panel versions when processing each profile.\n\nThe key scripts that need updating:\n1. `run_strategy_probe_guard.py` - generates probe guard reports\n2. `generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py` - generates today stock report\n\n\n3. `generate_strategy_probe_guard_summary.py` - generates summary\n4. Potentially `generate_control_tower.py` or `control_tower` related\n\nNow I'm looking at how `run_strategy_probe_guard.py` is structured to understand where the runtime risk state gets loaded and how to swap in the per-panel versions.","thinkingSignature":"0058e49802d94d8a4ac70dc41b5183642cf5da1ab441b035ef7c1b5f9bab4836"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1y6wo8w7sy6h_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":125,"limit":50,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13183,"output":269,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38684,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774991987831,"responseId":"061b6d73493f7e560bfa4c5f8ca92bfb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"79f18c45","parentId":"dc518da8","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:19:53.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1y6wo8w7sy6h_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    journal_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"journal\", profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\n    orders_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"orders\", profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\n    account_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"account_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug)\n    metrics_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"metrics\", profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\n    positions_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"positions_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug)\n\n    journal_df = read_csv(journal_path)\n    orders_df = read_csv(orders_path)\n    positions_df = read_csv(positions_path)\n    account_payload = load_json(account_path)\n    metrics_payload = load_json(metrics_path)\n    metrics = metrics_payload.get(\"metrics\", {}) or {}\n    runtime_state_path = REPORT_DIR / \"runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n    runtime_payload = load_json(runtime_state_path)\n    runtime_truth = get_runtime_truth(runtime_payload)\n\n    runtime_truth_state = str(runtime_truth.get(\"state\") or \"\")\n    runtime_trading_status = str(runtime_truth.get(\"trading_status\") or \"\")\n    runtime_buy_authorized = bool(runtime_truth.get(\"buy_authorized\")) if runtime_truth else None\n    runtime_can_execute_today = bool(runtime_truth.get(\"trading_ready\")) if runtime_truth else None\n    runtime_blocking_reason = str(\n        runtime_truth.get(\"trading_status_reason\")\n        or runtime_truth.get(\"state_reason\")\n        or runtime_payload.get(\"halt_reason\")\n        or \"\"\n    )\n\n    issues: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    drawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get(\"max_drawdown_pct\"), 0.0)\n    if drawdown_pct > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\"), 8.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH\", \"value\": drawdown_pct, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\")})\n\n    daily_ret_raw = journal_df.get(\"pnl_day\")\n    if daily_ret_raw is None:\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([], dtype=float)\n    elif isinstance(daily_ret_raw, (int, float)):\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([daily_ret_raw])\n    else:\n        daily_ret = pd.to_numeric(daily_ret_raw, errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0)\n    nav = parse_float(account_payload.get(\"nav\"), 0.0)\n    if nav > 0 and len(daily_ret) > 0:\n        ret_series = daily_ret.tail(20) / nav\n    else:\n        ret_series = pd.Series(dtype=float)\n\n    trailing_20d_ret = trailing_return_pct(ret_series)\n    if trailing_20d_ret < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\"), -5.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"RET_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_ret, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\")})\n\n\n[153 more lines in file. Use offset=175 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774991993048}}
