{"type":"message","id":"e783ba19","parentId":"cc1955fa","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:22:14.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The per-panel aggressive file has `halt_new_buy: false`, `buy_authorized: true`, `state: normal`. But the probe guard report shows `state: risk_off, buy_authorized: false`. This means `get_runtime_truth()` is NOT reading from `base_runtime.runtime_truth`.\n\nLet me look at the `runtime_state_schema.py` to understand what `get_runtime_truth()` reads.","thinkingSignature":"5ae21d92e22856589b74f964d030f250c4c2a4e7c0ebfd1680e9a0ab3415af11"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dyu5bae9nq9p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -n \"def get_runtime_truth\" scripts/runtime_state_schema.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24202,"output":142,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992130780,"responseId":"061b6e0239c6cef0b7fe876efe292f85"}}
