{"type":"message","id":"b6c2099f","parentId":"11afc3ce","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:22:17.414Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the `get_runtime_truth` function to understand what it reads.","thinkingSignature":"8eac526435b6020d41cdf5cc7097b119ecdc53622d775900e689bbec5d9ae356"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r80marhrkk0m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":427,"limit":60,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/runtime_state_schema.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24382,"output":85,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49699,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992134724,"responseId":"061b6e065f44add1312969f635e78241"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a9c1b37","parentId":"b6c2099f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:22:17.449Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r80marhrkk0m_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def get_runtime_truth(payload: dict[str, Any] | None) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if not isinstance(payload, dict):\n        return {}\n    truth = payload.get(\"runtime_truth\")\n    if isinstance(truth, dict) and truth.get(\"state\"):\n        return enrich_runtime_truth(truth)\n    latest_runtime = payload.get(\"latest_runtime\")\n    if isinstance(latest_runtime, dict):\n        nested = latest_runtime.get(\"runtime_truth\")\n        if isinstance(nested, dict) and nested.get(\"state\"):\n            return enrich_runtime_truth(nested)\n        return build_runtime_truth(\n            mode=str(latest_runtime.get(\"mode\") or \"\"),\n            risk_off=bool(latest_runtime.get(\"risk_off\")),\n            hard_stop=bool(latest_runtime.get(\"hard_stop\")),\n            halt_new_buy=bool(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_new_buy\")),\n            halt_reason=str(latest_runtime.get(\"halt_reason\") or \"\"),\n            gate_reasons=latest_runtime.get(\"gate_reasons\") or [],\n            source=\"runtime_payload_fallback\",\n        )\n    return {}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992137441}}
{"type":"message","id":"6fa6313d","parentId":"4a9c1b37","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:22:25.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! `get_runtime_truth()` first checks for a top-level `runtime_truth` key in the payload. If not found, it checks for `latest_runtime.runtime_truth`. But my per-panel files don't have a top-level `runtime_truth` key, and they also don't have `latest_runtime`.\n\nWait - but they DO have `base_runtime.runtime_truth`. The function checks `payload.get(\"runtime_truth\")` first (top-level), then `payload.get(\"latest_runtime\")`. Neither matches my per-panel structure which has `base_runtime.runtime_truth`.\n\nSo my per-panel files should fall through to the `latest_runtime` case... but `latest_runtime` is also not present. \n\nThat means `get_runtime_truth()` returns `{}`, yet the probe guard output shows `state: risk_off, buy_authorized: false`. Something else must be providing these values. Looking at `run_strategy_probe_guard.py`, it calls `get_runtime_truth(runtime_payload)` and then extracts `runtime_truth_state`, `runtime_trading_status`, `runtime_buy_authorized`, `runtime_can_execute_today`, and `runtime_blocking_reason` from the result.\n\nBut the actual probe guard JSON has `runtime_truth` nested directly at the top level with `state: risk_off`, so maybe `run_strategy_probe_guard.py` is populating those fields differently than I thought. I need to look at how that script actually builds the `runtime_truth` object that gets written to the JSON.","thinkingSignature":"167b38852cf4d2bb3577dd75e160cbcf610ff14a6d8ae070e0d1102facc0cfaa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ilfp1maav4p6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":139,"limit":60,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24700,"output":371,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50303,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992137450,"responseId":"061b6e097a94272221b2fa7bafaaba12"}}
{"type":"message","id":"88233c96","parentId":"6fa6313d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:22:26.031Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ilfp1maav4p6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    if panel_risk_path.exists():\n        runtime_state_path = panel_risk_path\n    else:\n        runtime_state_path = REPORT_DIR / \"runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n    runtime_payload = load_json(runtime_state_path)\n    runtime_truth = get_runtime_truth(runtime_payload)\n\n    runtime_truth_state = str(runtime_truth.get(\"state\") or \"\")\n    runtime_trading_status = str(runtime_truth.get(\"trading_status\") or \"\")\n    runtime_buy_authorized = bool(runtime_truth.get(\"buy_authorized\")) if runtime_truth else None\n    runtime_can_execute_today = bool(runtime_truth.get(\"trading_ready\")) if runtime_truth else None\n    runtime_blocking_reason = str(\n        runtime_truth.get(\"trading_status_reason\")\n        or runtime_truth.get(\"state_reason\")\n        or runtime_payload.get(\"halt_reason\")\n        or \"\"\n    )\n\n    issues: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    drawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get(\"max_drawdown_pct\"), 0.0)\n    if drawdown_pct > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\"), 8.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH\", \"value\": drawdown_pct, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\")})\n\n    daily_ret_raw = journal_df.get(\"pnl_day\")\n    if daily_ret_raw is None:\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([], dtype=float)\n    elif isinstance(daily_ret_raw, (int, float)):\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([daily_ret_raw])\n    else:\n        daily_ret = pd.to_numeric(daily_ret_raw, errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0)\n    nav = parse_float(account_payload.get(\"nav\"), 0.0)\n    if nav > 0 and len(daily_ret) > 0:\n        ret_series = daily_ret.tail(20) / nav\n    else:\n        ret_series = pd.Series(dtype=float)\n\n    trailing_20d_ret = trailing_return_pct(ret_series)\n    if trailing_20d_ret < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\"), -5.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"RET_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_ret, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\")})\n\n    trailing_20d_sharpe = round(annualized_sharpe(ret_series.tail(20)), 3) if not ret_series.empty else 0.0\n    if trailing_20d_sharpe < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\"), 0.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"SHARPE_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_sharpe, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\")})\n\n    avg_slippage = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(\"slippage\"), errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0).mean()), 2) if not journal_df.empty else 0.0\n    if avg_slippage > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\"), 200.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_SLIPPAGE_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_slippage, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\")})\n\n    turnover_col = \"weight_after\"\n    avg_turnover = 0.0\n    if turnover_col in journal_df.columns and not journal_df.empty:\n        avg_turnover = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(turnover_col), errors=\"coerce\").diff().abs().fillna(0.0).mean()), 4)\n    if avg_turnover > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\"), 0.12):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_TURNOVER_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_turnover, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\")})\n\n    journal_records = int(len(journal_df))\n    runtime_halt_blocked_orders = False\n    if journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n        if not orders_df.empty:\n\n[134 more lines in file. Use offset=199 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992146023}}
