{"type":"message","id":"c2764b7b","parentId":"6562e9ac","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:00.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the logic at lines 204, 225-239:\n```python\n    if ... runtime_trading_status in {\"BUY_HALT\", \"FULL_HALT\"}:\n        ...\n        status = \"RED\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"halt\"\n    elif runtime_trading_status in {\"RISK_OFF\", \"CAUTIOUS\"}:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif runtime_trading_status == \"TRADING\":\n        status = \"GREEN\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n```\n\nSo if `runtime_trading_status` is \"TRADING\", it should be GREEN. \n\nBut the output shows RED, which means `runtime_trading_status` must actually be \"BUY_HALT\". Let me trace through the debug output again—the `runtime_truth` object has `state='normal'` and `trading_status='TRADING'`, so if `get_runtime_truth()` is returning this correctly, then `runtime_truth.get('trading_status')` should be 'TRADING', not 'BUY_HALT'. Something's not adding up here.\n\nLooking at the conditional logic around lines 225-239, if `runtime_trading_status` were 'TRADING', the status would be set to GREEN. But the output is RED, which means either the truth object is different than what I'm seeing, or there's a different code path being taken. Let me check if there's an override happening before this conditional block, or if the status is being set to RED somewhere else entirely.","thinkingSignature":"25262188d5dd01e781b35a49571a47ce6155854506524bc022f5b8f7600d40f8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7qb44tlnhpwk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":195,"limit":50,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35900,"output":388,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61520,"cost":{"input":0,"