{"type":"message","id":"9365793b","parentId":"c2764b7b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:00.804Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7qb44tlnhpwk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_TURNOVER_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_turnover, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\")})\n\n    journal_records = int(len(journal_df))\n    runtime_halt_blocked_orders = False\n    if journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n        if not orders_df.empty:\n            runtime_halt_blocked_orders = (\n                bool(runtime_truth)\n                and runtime_buy_authorized is False\n                and runtime_trading_status in {\"BUY_HALT\", \"FULL_HALT\"}\n            )\n            if runtime_halt_blocked_orders:\n                issues.append(\n                    {\n                        \"level\": \"INFO\",\n                        \"code\": \"PLANNED_ORDERS_BLOCKED_BY_RUNTIME_HALT\",\n                        \"value\": int(len(orders_df)),\n                        \"limit\": 0,\n                    }\n                )\n            else:\n                issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", \"value\": int(len(orders_df)), \"limit\": 0})\n        else:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"NO_ACTIVITY_DAY\", \"value\": journal_records, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\")})\n\n    error_trade_count = int(journal_df.get(\"risk_reason\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).astype(str).str.contains(\"error|reject|failed\", case=False, na=False).sum()) if not journal_df.empty else 0\n    if error_trade_count > int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\"), 0.0)):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH\", \"value\": error_trade_count, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\")})\n\n    observation_days = int(cfg.get(\"admission\", {}).get(\"paper_observation_min_days\", 20))\n    status = \"GREEN\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"normal\"\n    if any(item[\"level\"] == \"RED\" for item in issues):\n        status = \"RED\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"halt\"\n    elif any(item[\"level\"] == \"YELLOW\" for item in issues):\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif runtime_halt_blocked_orders:\n        status = \"GREEN\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n    elif journal_records < observation_days:\n        # Journal 不足 observation_days 天数，但不构成告警；次日模式改为 observe\n        status = \"GREEN\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n\n    payload = {\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"),\n        \"config\": str(cfg_path),\n        \"date_tag\": date_tag,\n\n[90 more lines in file. Use offset=245 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992300795}}
{"type":"message","id":"96b466fe","parentId":"9365793b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:11.630Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! The status is determined by `issues` first:\n\n```python\nif any(item[\"level\"] == \"RED\" for item in issues):\n    status = \"RED\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"halt\"\n```\n\nSo there must be a RED issue that's being added. The `runtime_truth` being correct (GREEN/TRADING) doesn't matter if there are RED issues.\n\nLet me check what issues are being raised. Looking at the code:\n1. `MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH` - could be RED\n2. `RET_20D_BREACH` - could be RED\n3. `SHARPE_20D_BREACH` - could be YELLOW\n\n\n4. `AVG_SLIPPAGE_BREACH` - could be YELLOW\n5. `AVG_TURNOVER_BREACH` - could be YELLOW\n6. `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` - could be RED\n7. `ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH` - could be RED\n\nFor aggressive, the `MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH` check compares `drawdown_pct` against `thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\")`, so I need to verify what threshold is actually set for this profile.\n\nLooking at the defensive config, the drawdown threshold is 8.0, but the aggressive profile likely has a higher threshold like 15 or 20. Let me check what the actual threshold is.","thinkingSignature":"4e381577ad5bdb330f8f39ac98ecc79955c2ce358dc9409b24c3741f0d5510d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4haunyeq58q1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nimport json\ncfg = json.load(open('config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json'))\nthresholds = cfg.get('thresholds', {}) or {}\nprint('paper_max_drawdown_pct:', thresholds.get('paper_max_drawdown_pct'))\nprint('paper_20d_return_floor_pct:', thresholds.get('paper_20d_return_floor_pct'))\n\" && python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd = json.load(open('research/reports/paper_aggressive_metrics_20260330.json'))\nm = d.get('metrics', {})\nprint('max_drawdown_pct:', m.get('max_drawdown_pct'))\nprint('pnl_20d:', m.get('pnl_20d'))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":36936,"output":511,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992300804,"responseId":"061b6eade5a77f4237918ef9af01ec68"}}
