{"type":"message","id":"8bb8ad3e","parentId":"650f5bbd","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:45.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`max_drawdown_pct = 0.39%` which is very low. This is clearly not causing a RED issue. So the RED status must be coming from another check.\n\nLet me look at what checks cause RED:\n1. `MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH` - `0.39 > parse_float(None, 8.0) = 8.0` → NO\n2. `RET_20D_BREACH` - `trailing_20d_ret < ...` \n3. `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` - Let me check this\n\nFor `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS`:\n\n\nThe condition checks if journal_records is at or below the threshold (defaulting to 0) AND positions are empty. Since journal_records should be greater than 0, this shouldn't trigger. The RED status might actually be coming from the runtime halt check instead.\n\nLooking at the logic more carefully: if journal_records ≤ 0 and positions_df is empty, but there are orders in the queue, then runtime_halt_blocked_orders gets set to True only if runtime_truth exists, buy_authorized is False, and trading_status is in the halt states. For aggressive mode, buy_authorized is True and trading_status is 'TRADING', so this condition fails and runtime_halt_blocked_orders becomes False—which means the RED status must be coming from elsewhere.\n\nI'm realizing the RED issue might stem from a different check like `ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH` that I haven't examined yet. Let me run the script with debug output to see what issues are actually being raised.","thinkingSignature":"d139228f78f3c06c9f1a4b146f732e8d05213ba343351a5bb9d8b50342d4ab9f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e7ax4s6ppign_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys, pandas as pd\nsys.path.insert(0, 'scripts')\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom paper_profile_utils import report_path\nfrom runtime_state_schema import get_runtime_truth\nfrom parse import parse_float\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path('.')\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'research' / 'reports'\n\ndef load_json(path):\n    if not path.exists(): return {}\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\nprofile_slug = 'aggressive'\ndate_tag = '20260330'\n\njournal_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'journal', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\norders_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'orders', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\naccount_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'account_latest', profile_slug=profile_slug)\nmetrics_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'metrics', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag)\npositions_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'positions_latest', profile_slug=profile_slug)\n\njournal_df = pd.read_csv(journal_path) if journal_path.exists() else pd.DataFrame()\norders_df = pd.read_csv(orders_path) if orders_path.exists() else pd.DataFrame()\npositions_df = pd.read_csv(positions_path) if positions_path.exists() else pd.DataFrame()\naccount_payload = load_json(account_path)\nmetrics_payload = load_json(metrics_path)\nmetrics = metrics_payload.get('metrics', {}) or {}\n\npanel_risk_path = REPORT_DIR / f'runtime_risk_state_latest_{profile_slug}.json'\nruntime_payload = load_json(panel_risk_path if panel_risk_path.exists() else REPORT_DIR / 'runtime_risk_state_latest.json')\nruntime_truth = get_runtime_truth(runtime_payload)\nprint('runtime_truth:', json.dumps(runtime_truth, indent=2)[:200])\n\ncfg = json.load(open('config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json'))\nthresholds = cfg.get('thresholds', {}) or {}\n\ndrawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get('max_drawdown_pct'), 0.0)\nprint('drawdown_pct:', drawdown_pct, 'threshold:', thresholds.get('paper_max_drawdown_pct'))\n\njournal_records = int(len(journal_df))\nprint('journal_records:', journal_records, 'positions_empty:', positions_df.empty, 'orders_empty:', orders_df.empty)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38435,"output":893,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64560,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992326617,"responseId":"061b6ec6350c50b970303bb2ae8bc73a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"48d718ee","parentId":"8bb8ad3e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:45.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e7ax4s6ppign_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"<string>\", line 7, in <module>\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'parse'\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":226,"aggregated":"Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"<string>\", line 7, in <module>\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'parse'\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992345324}}
{"type":"message","id":"356ffa03","parentId":"48d718ee","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:25:59.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `parse` module isn't available. Let me use a different approach.","thinkingSignature":"49053ba4ce8404e29bae9e374a87d392c1029238eb3f5012a4e66ce1ba13ded8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2ozog1my4zj6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys, pandas as pd\nsys.path.insert(0, 'scripts')\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom paper_profile_utils import report_path\nfrom runtime_state_schema import get_runtime_truth\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path('.')\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'research' / 'reports'\n\ndef load_json(path):\n    if not path.exists(): return {}\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\ndef parse_float(v, default=0.0):\n    try: return float(v)\n    except: return default\n\nprofile_slug = 'aggressive'\ndate_tag = '20260330'\n\njournal_df = pd.read_csv(report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'journal', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag))\norders_df = pd.read_csv(report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'orders', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag))\npositions_df = pd.read_csv(report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'positions_latest', profile_slug=profile_slug))\naccount_payload = load_json(report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'account_latest', profile_slug=profile_slug))\nmetrics_payload = load_json(report_path(REPORT_DIR, 'metrics', profile_slug=profile_slug, date_tag=date_tag))\nmetrics = metrics_payload.get('metrics', {}) or {}\n\npanel_risk_path = REPORT_DIR / f'runtime_risk_state_latest_{profile_slug}.json'\nruntime_payload = load_json(panel_risk_path if panel_risk_path.exists() else REPORT_DIR / 'runtime_risk_state_latest.json')\nruntime_truth = get_runtime_truth(runtime_payload)\n\ncfg = json.load(open('config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json'))\nthresholds = cfg.get('thresholds', {}) or {}\n\nissues = []\ndrawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get('max_drawdown_pct'), 0.0)\nth_dd = parse_float(thresholds.get('paper_max_drawdown_pct'), 8.0)\nprint(f'drawdown_pct={drawdown_pct} > th={th_dd}? {drawdown_pct > th_dd}')\nif drawdown_pct > th_dd:\n    issues.append({'level':'RED','code':'MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH','value':drawdown_pct})\n\njournal_records = len(journal_df)\nprint(f'journal_records={journal_records}, positions_empty={positions_df.empty}, orders_empty={orders_df.empty}')\nif journal_records <= 0 and positions_df.empty:\n    if not orders_df.empty:\n        rt_buy = runtime_truth.get('buy_authorized')\n        rt_status = runtime_truth.get('trading_status')\n        print(f'runtime halt check: buy_auth={rt_buy}, status={rt_status}')\n        if rt_buy is False and rt_status in {'BUY_HALT','FULL_HALT'}:\n            issues.append({'level':'INFO','code':'PLANNED_ORDERS_BLOCKED_BY_RUNTIME_HALT'})\n        else:\n            issues.append({'level':'RED','code':'NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS'})\n\nprint('issues:', issues)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39382,"output":711,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992345330,"responseId":"061b6ed984ed339864143d7b35276cef"}}
