{"type":"message","id":"dc91400e","parentId":"18348b36","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:26:09.788Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now: `journal_records=0` but `orders_df` is not empty. And since `buy_authorized=True` and `trading_status=TRADING` (per-panel), it goes to the `else` branch with `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS: RED`.\n\nThe condition is:\n```python\nif journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n```\n\nWith `journal_records=0` and `paper_missing_journal_records_cap=None` → defaults to `0.0` → `int(0.0) = 0`.\n\n\nSo `0 <= 0` is True, positions is empty, orders exist, but `runtime_halt_blocked_orders=False` because per-panel is `buy_authorized=True, trading_status=TRADING`. This triggers the RED issue `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS`.\n\nThe real problem is that the `paper_missing_journal_records_cap` threshold defaults to 0, which means any day with zero journal records and open orders gets flagged RED. I need to either increase that threshold or reconsider the logic around what constitutes a missing journal versus an absence of trading activity.\n\nSince today is April 1, 2026 and the date_tag is 20260330, there's likely no journal file for today yet—which is expected. The threshold should probably be 1 or 2 to account for this normal scenario where we haven't traded today.","thinkingSignature":"bdc8194f5f87f7bcf73ae9111cbada486bba8fd01d2dd209528c0d079f4b6cbe"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it. The issue: `journal_records=0` but `orders` pending → `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS: RED`. The T02 fix should prevent this by checking runtime halt. But since aggressive now has `buy_authorized=True`, the fallback RED fires. I need to fix the T02 logic in this block:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_df3nom5x540l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":199,"limit":25,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40179,"output":459,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992359276,"responseId":"061b6ee7f0c1069931eb5e24faabfc5f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"40654753","parentId":"dc91400e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:26:09.828Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_df3nom5x540l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    if journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n        if not orders_df.empty:\n            runtime_halt_blocked_orders = (\n                bool(runtime_truth)\n                and runtime_buy_authorized is False\n                and runtime_trading_status in {\"BUY_HALT\", \"FULL_HALT\"}\n            )\n            if runtime_halt_blocked_orders:\n                issues.append(\n                    {\n                        \"level\": \"INFO\",\n                        \"code\": \"PLANNED_ORDERS_BLOCKED_BY_RUNTIME_HALT\",\n                        \"value\": int(len(orders_df)),\n                        \"limit\": 0,\n                    }\n                )\n            else:\n                issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", \"value\": int(len(orders_df)), \"limit\": 0})\n        else:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"NO_ACTIVITY_DAY\", \"value\": journal_records, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\")})\n\n    error_trade_count = int(journal_df.get(\"risk_reason\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).astype(str).str.contains(\"error|reject|failed\", case=False, na=False).sum()) if not journal_df.empty else 0\n    if error_trade_count > int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\"), 0.0)):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH\", \"value\": error_trade_count, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\")})\n\n\n[111 more lines in file. Use offset=224 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992369820}}
{"type":"message","id":"e464bdc3","parentId":"40654753","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:26:19.991Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is: if `journal_records=0` and there are pending orders, the script checks:\n1. Is `runtime_buy_authorized is False`? → For aggressive per-panel, it's `True` (because `halt_new_buy=False`).\n2. So `runtime_halt_blocked_orders = False`.\n3. Which triggers `else: issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", ...})`\n\nBut the real issue is that today is April 1 - there's no trading journal for today because markets are closed (A股清明节). So `journal_records=0` is NORMAL, not an error. \n\nThe pending orders in the file are probably from yesterday. The RED flag `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` is incorrectly firing because the script doesn't account for non-trading days. I need to add a check: if today isn't a trading day, the missing journal shouldn't trigger an error since markets are closed.\n\nBut wait—`paper_missing_journal_records_cap` is a configuration threshold, so maybe I should look at how T02 addressed this. The real distinction T02 was trying to make was between orders blocked by runtime halt (should be INFO) versus orders existing when there's no journal but no runtime halt (should be RED for aggressive panels, but actually this is normal for non-trading days). So the RED classification only makes sense if it's a trading day AND there's no journal AND runtime halt isn't blocking. I need to add a trading day check.","thinkingSignature":"c2b7b4f650bae43b994a7735bd34e58dfa991947f6bb1678bcbe97a2371100df"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zpgyxvq8i40t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -n \"is_trading_day\\|trade_date\\|market_open\\|trading_day\" scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41017,"output":396,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992369829,"responseId":"061b6ef1fbf20d46e409875a26286b68"}}
