{"type":"message","id":"60e76e6c","parentId":"ef702121","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:29:27.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The latest files are correct. Now let me look at the summary reading logic more carefully. The summary uses `report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"probe_guard\", ...)` which generates a path like `paper_${profile_slug}_probe_guard_${date_tag}.json`. The date_tag comes from `latest_date_tag()`. Since the latest date is 20260401 (today, as there's no dated file for aggressive), it reads `paper_aggressive_probe_guard_20260401.json` which doesn't exist (only `_20260330.json` and `_latest.json` exist). \n\nSo the issue is that the latest_date_tag function extracts 20260401 from the file names (since there's no 8-digit number in `paper_exit_tight_probe_guard_latest.json`, it returns today's date 20260401), and then tries to read `paper_aggressive_probe_guard_20260401.json` which doesn't exist.\n \nThe real problem is that `_latest.json` files are the ones that actually have content, but the reading logic only looks for dated files. I need to fix `latest_date_tag()` to prioritize `_latest.json` files, or better yet, have it read from those directly instead of relying on date extraction.","thinkingSignature":"0fd7b97eb4f2dc5783d043fd7c9fb3ccd1cf9ec90e07c99f98cc7d9fe1ddea10"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xixbkjbstuqc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":61,"limit":50,"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_strategy_probe_guard_summary.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41680,"output":324,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67236,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992559529,"responseId":"061b6fafe5a9dc3b6eaecefa24570b97"}}
{"type":"message","id":"99f496ce","parentId":"60e76e6c","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:29:27.616Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xixbkjbstuqc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def main() -> None:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"汇总三套 profile guard 状态\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--date\", default=\"\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--push\", action=\"store_true\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    date_tag = args.date.strip() or latest_date_tag()\n    rows: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    for cfg_path in DEFAULT_CONFIGS:\n        cfg = load_json(cfg_path)\n        profile_slug = str(cfg.get(\"profile_slug\") or \"\").strip()\n        report_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"paper_{profile_slug}_probe_guard_{date_tag}.json\"\n        payload = load_json(report_path)\n        stats = payload.get(\"stats\", {}) or {}\n        issues = payload.get(\"issues\", []) or []\n        runtime_truth = payload.get(\"runtime_truth\", {}) or {}\n        rows.append(\n            {\n                \"profile_slug\": profile_slug,\n                \"profile_name\": cfg.get(\"profile_name\", profile_slug),\n                \"status\": payload.get(\"status\", \"NO_DATA\"),\n                \"tomorrow_mode\": payload.get(\"tomorrow_mode\", \"-\"),\n                \"runtime_truth_state\": runtime_truth.get(\"state\"),\n                \"trading_status\": runtime_truth.get(\"trading_status\"),\n                \"can_execute_today\": runtime_truth.get(\"can_execute_today\"),\n                \"buy_authorized\": runtime_truth.get(\"buy_authorized\"),\n                \"blocking_reason\": runtime_truth.get(\"blocking_reason\"),\n                \"planned_orders\": stats.get(\"planned_orders\", 0),\n                \"journal_records\": stats.get(\"journal_records\", 0),\n                \"position_count\": stats.get(\"position_count\", 0),\n                \"nav\": stats.get(\"nav\", 0.0),\n                \"max_drawdown_pct\": stats.get(\"max_drawdown_pct\", 0.0),\n                \"trailing_20d_return_pct\": stats.get(\"trailing_20d_return_pct\", 0.0),\n                \"trailing_20d_sharpe\": stats.get(\"trailing_20d_sharpe\", 0.0),\n                \"avg_slippage\": stats.get(\"avg_slippage\", 0.0),\n                \"issue_count\": len(issues),\n                \"issue_codes\": \",\".join(str(item.get(\"code\", \"\")) for item in issues if item.get(\"code\")),\n                \"report_json\": str(report_path),\n            }\n        )\n\n    df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n    status_rank = {\"RED\": 3, \"YELLOW\": 2, \"GREEN\": 1, \"NO_DATA\": 0}\n    df[\"status_rank\"] = df[\"status\"].map(status_rank).fillna(0).astype(int)\n    portfolio_status = df.sort_values([\"status_rank\", \"profile_slug\"], ascending=[False, True]).iloc[0][\"status\"] if not df.empty else \"NO_DATA\"\n    halt_count = int((df[\"tomorrow_mode\"] == \"halt\").sum()) if not df.empty else 0\n\n    out_csv = REPORT_DIR / f\"strategy_probe_guard_summary_{date_tag}.csv\"\n    out_json = REPORT_DIR / f\"strategy_probe_guard_summary_{date_tag}.json\"\n\n[52 more lines in file. Use offset=111 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774992567608}}
{"type":"message","id":"f12423be","parentId":"99f496ce","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:29:36.527Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue clearly now. The summary script at line 73 constructs the report path as:\n```\nreport_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"paper_{profile_slug}_probe_guard_{date_tag}.json\"\n```\n\nAnd `date_tag` comes from `latest_date_tag()` which returned `20260401` (today's date) because it only found `paper_exit_tight_probe_guard_latest.json` as the latest file.\n\nSo it tries to read `paper_aggressive_probe_guard_20260401.json` which doesn't exist → `payload = {}` → all fields are None.\n\nThe fix: change the reading logic to first try `_latest.json` if the dated file doesn't exist. \n\nNow I'll implement this by modifying the report path construction to check for the `_latest.json` variant first before falling back to the dated version.","thinkingSignature":"403cfb0344c492749871d1c1997c9b4694eb2da6ebb0e03a8f5f62f0e828c422"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b051dj1p59zc_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_strategy_probe_guard_summary.py","old_string":"    for cfg_path in DEFAULT_CONFIGS:\n        cfg = load_json(cfg_path)\n        profile_slug = str(cfg.get(\"profile_slug\") or \"\").strip()\n        report_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"paper_{profile_slug}_probe_guard_{date_tag}.json\"\n        payload = load_json(report_path)","newString":"    for cfg_path in DEFAULT_CONFIGS:\n        cfg = load_json(cfg_path)\n        profile_slug = str(cfg.get(\"profile_slug\") or \"\").strip()\n        # T05 fix: first try _latest.json (most recent result), fall back to dated file\n        dated_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"paper_{profile_slug}_probe_guard_{date_tag}.json\"\n        latest_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"paper_{profile_slug}_probe_guard_latest.json\"\n        report_path = latest_path if latest_path.exists() else (dated_pa