{"type":"message","id":"99c2f5fa","parentId":"62431393","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:30:53.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the config files don't have probe_budget or candidate_source settings. These must be defined in the panel_profile_registry or in the merge/bidding scripts. Let me look at the PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG again - it already has `candidate_source_tag` and `probe_budget_tag` fields. These are the target config we want to implement.\n\nBut the actual code that reads and uses these tags is not yet implemented. The key insight is:\n1. The per-panel runtime risk truth is now working (Step 1 done)\n2. The probe budget and candidate source tags are defined in `PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG`\n\n\n3. I need to trace through the signal flow to find where these tags are actually consumed - they're referenced in the merge process and the bidding/ranking logic, but I need to check the scripts like `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py` to see if they're being read there.","thinkingSignature":"26edac2cd5180996183a90e4c167bb4931c6817fcd7532a17baa0518f0a256a5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wdzm4hhcgtqg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -n \"probe_budget_tag\\|candidate_source_tag\\|aggressive_high_elasticity\\|balanced_mid_quality\\|defensive_top_quality\" scripts/*.py 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46795,"output":283,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992644660,"responseId":"061b700476eb4e5b470bffc9ae838c4f"}}
