{"type":"message","id":"5b4aab70","parentId":"b72e8161","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:31:00.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tags are defined in `panel_profile_registry.py` but not yet used in any scripts. Let me check the apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py to see how signals are selected and if there's a ranking gate or candidate source concept.\n\nActually, looking at the T05 blueprint, the key point for candidate source separation is:\n- aggressive: keeps high-elasticity smallcaps from merged_signals\n- balanced: only mid+ quality, no overbuying\n- defensive: only strongest pass candidates\n\nThis would require changes to the signal merging/filtering stage, not just the risk stage. This is a larger change.\n\nLet me focus on what's achievable in the next step - the probe budget tags. Let me look at where probe budget is actually used.","thinkingSignature":"cf3dce76ee7284c38c90333e06e0188128d7a7864db83939521850d1d182a4c4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cedtmbk0asm8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && grep -rn \"probe_budget\\|probe_limit\\|max_probe\" scripts/*.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"__pycache__\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47274,"output":236,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72742,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992654149,"responseId":"061b700e16f9e98f8bdc3fdf7b735969"}}
