{"type":"message","id":"34f757db","parentId":"fde29c95","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:31:15.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The probe budget is computed in `run_live_execution_v1.py` but it uses `cautious_probe_cfg` which is from the live config. The per-panel differences in probe budget would need changes at the live execution level.\n\nFor the current session, let me check what's the next actionable step for T05 that I can complete. The T05 blueprint says:\n\n1. ✅ Per-panel runtime risk truth (done)\n2. (pending) Candidate source separation - this requires changes to the merge/filter scripts\n3. (pending) Probe budget台阶 - this requires changes to live execution config\n4. (pending) alpha55 single-column fix\n\n\n5. \nThe critical fix is Step 2 - separating candidate sources. Without this, all three panels still draw from the same merged_signals, so they're not truly independent. But this touches the signal merge pipeline, which is complex. Let me examine what the signal merge process looks like to understand where the separation should happen.","thinkingSignature":"e37e810427d1369d439aa5d48df8c504db108f5a54076c2f135ca540acbcacf7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1c3o0plnt1kv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && ls signals/merged/ 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48255,"output":260,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992669641,"responseId":"061b701d878cefbe1f34bd1f09ac5951"}}
