{"type":"message","id":"e3aabb3b","parentId":"c9d11631","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:31:25.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the merged signals are dated CSV files. The three profiles (aggressive/balanced/defensive) currently all use the same `merged_signals_YYYYMMDD.csv`. For the candidate source separation to work, we'd need:\n- `merged_signals_aggressive_YYYYMMDD.csv` (high elasticity candidates)\n- `merged_signals_balanced_YYYYMMDD.csv` (mid quality)\n- `merged_signals_defensive_YYYYMMDD.csv` (top quality only)\n\nBut creating these separate merged signals would require changes to the merge pipeline script that generates them. This is a significant change.\n \nI should verify that the per-panel halt is functioning correctly first. For T05's next phase, the most practical step would be to define the probe budget tiers in the panel registry and update the live execution to reference per-panel probe budget values. The T05 blueprint already specifies these tiers—aggressive allows higher probe exposure while balanced and defensive have progressively lower limits—so implementing this would be straightforward.\n\nThe key blocker is that without candidate source separation, all three panels still pull from the same merged signals, which defeats the purpose of per-panel risk management. However, the candidate source separation is a more substantial architectural change. For now, I should focus on what can be verified immediately—checking whether the per-panel halt is actually producing different outcomes—while acknowledging that the candidate source work is the critical missing piece for the next iteration.","thinkingSignature":"645bd23545daee8da209d77b171885db5b3e15866654a99b396f78ed8fe5b727"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iobb2cmezx0z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd = json.load(open('research/reports/control_tower_daily_latest.json'))\nprint('Top keys:', list(d.keys())[:10])\nprofiles = d.get('profiles', d.get('panel_status', {}))\nif isinstance(profiles, dict):\n    for k,v in profiles.items():\n        rt = v.get('runtime_truth', {})\n        print(f'{k}: halt={rt.get(\\\"halt_new_buy\\\")}, risk_off={rt.get(\\\"risk_off\\\")}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48585,"output":450,"cacheRead":25232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74267,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774992676030,"responseId":"061b7024b4996d6162168f257f7f4c35"}}
